# Component Patterns

## Reusable Component Guidelines

### Component Wrapper Pattern

```tsx
const StyledView = ({ size, className, ...props }) => (
  <View
    className={clsx("rounded-xl", size === "small" && "w-[50px]", className)}
    {...props}
  />
);
```

### Button Components

- Use TouchableOpacity/Pressable + className
- Use conditional classes for size variants
- Include Text component with appropriate styling

### Icon Components

- Keep using react-native-vector-icons or similar
- Add className support for styling
- Use Tailwind color classes instead of theme tokens

## Component Props Pattern

Always support these props for consistency:

```tsx
interface ComponentProps {
  className?: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  // ... other specific props
}
```

Note: `vh` and `vw` can be used in alternative to `DEVICE_WIDTH` and `DEVICE_HEIGHT`

## Component Playground

To implement component playground file follow the same pattern in `components/Button/Button.playground.tsx`

## Testing Requirements

- Test components on both iOS and Android
- Verify dark mode support with `dark:` classes
- Check responsive behavior if applicable
